result.execSummary:
The defendant Alexander J. Corona was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Probation may not end sooner than one year. No Expungement.

miscConds.notes:
Pay restitution in the amount of $3,180.00 and restitution surcharge. To be paid within first six (6) months of probation. 
----------------------------------

Pay court costs.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment may be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.
----------------------------------

No alcohol.  No illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia.  Not to operate a motor vehicle without a valid driver's license. No contact with Jayme Brovold. 
----------------------------------

Counseling as recommended by Probation Agent.   Pursuant to sec. 973.046(1r), the defendant is required to pay $200.00 DNA surcharge. The defendant must pay Department of Corrections Supervision fees.
----------------------------------

timeConds.notes: The defendant is to complete a total of one-hundred (100) hours of community service work during his period of probation with NO BUYOUT.
